                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Sefer ha-Shorashim</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Can_Or_67-item1" n="1">
                            <locus>ff. 1r-233r</locus>
                            <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/100213323">Kimhi, David, approximately
                                1160-approximately 1235   קמחי, דוד בן יוסף</author>
                            <title>Sefer ha-Shorashim   <foreign xml:lang="he">ספר השורשים </foreign>
                     </title>
                            <note>On the margins at the beginning and on some leaves in the middle
                                of the MS there are omissions and biblical referenes by an Italian
                                hand. Glosses written in an Italian mid-late 15th-century
                                hand.</note>
                            <note>The document on fol. 234v dated 1417 (in Portuguese) might be by
                                the scribe's grandson. </note>

                            <colophon>Colophon on fol. 231r: <foreign xml:lang="he">יצחק בן יוסף
                                    זרקו כתב בלישבואה שנת ל"ח</foreign>. The script seems to be of a
                                later period. Perhaps the hundreds were omitted in the colophon and
                                the date should be 5[1]38=<date calendar="Gregorian">1378</date>?</colophon>
                            <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                        </msItem>


                    </msContents>
